The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 19 April is 41,701 (4,826.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 14 April, there were 132 new confirmed cases (15.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 April, there were 135 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 2% (3 fewer cases).
